oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Hoflund's Syndrome: The Consequence of Failure in the Selective Retention of Particles in the Reticulo-Rumen?
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Rehage, J.
Stockhofe-Zurwieden, N.
Kaske, M.
Yalzin, E.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: reticule-rumen
pathogenesis
Hoflund's syndrome
particles
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The objective of this study was to investigate whether a failure in the ability to retain selectively particles in the reticule-rumen plays a role in the pathogenesis of HOFLUND's syndrome.
